alert.note: Alert for Northern Humboldt Coast (California) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: High Wind Warning issued March 27 at 8:48AM PDT until March 28 at 1:00AM PDT by NWS Eureka
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 3 PM THIS AFTERNOON TO 1 AM PDT TUESDAY... ...FREEZE WARNING WILL EXPIRE AT 9 AM PDT THIS MORNING... * WHAT...Southeast winds 30 to 40 mph with gusts up to 60 mph expected. * WHERE...Northern Humboldt Coast County. * WHEN...From 3 PM this afternoon to 1 AM PDT Tuesday. * IMPACTS...Damaging winds will blow down trees and power lines. Widespread power outages are expected. Travel will be difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.
info.instruction: People should avoid being outside in forested areas and around trees and branches. If possible, remain in the lower levels of your home during the windstorm, and avoid windows. Use caution if you must drive.
